OVERVIEW: List groups in the project as a tree structure

Lists all groups in the Xcode project as a tree structure.
By default shows a tree structure. Use --show-names to see both simple names
and full paths for use with other commands.

Examples:
  xcodeproj-cli list-groups
  xcodeproj-cli list-groups --show-names

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli list-groups [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] [--show-names]

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  --show-names            Show both tree structure and usable names
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

